## Fields (compensation)

- `salary_min` — integer, or `null`.
- `salary_max` — integer, or `null`.
- `salary_currency` — ISO 4217 (e.g. `"EUR"`, `"USD"`, `"GBP"`), or `null`.
- `salary_period` — one of: `"hour"`, `"day"`, `"week"`, `"month"`, `"year"`, `"project"`, or `null`.
- `salary_transparency` — one of: `"shown"`, `"range_in_description"`, `"not_shown"`, or `null`.
- `compensation_type` — one of: `"salary"`, `"hourly"`, `"commission_only"`, `"salary_plus_commission"`, `"tips_plus_base"`, `"piece_rate"`, `"stipend"`, `"fee_per_service"`, `"retainer"`, `"grant_funded"`, or `null`.
- `equity_offered` — `true` / `false` / `null`. `null` when not mentioned; only `false` if the text explicitly denies it.

## Fields (location / visa)

- `remote_policy` — one of: `"onsite"`, `"hybrid"`, `"remote"`, `"remote_anywhere"`, `"unclear"`, or `null`. Never guess; default to `null` if not clearly stated.
- `remote_region` — free-text region if remote is region-bounded (e.g. `"EU"`, `"UK"`, `"EEA"`, `"US"`, `"APAC"`, `"LATAM"`, `"MENA"`, `"ANZ"`, `"Nordics"`, country names, `"global"`), else `null`.
- `relocation_assistance` — `true` / `false` / `null`.
- `visa_sponsorship` — one of: `"yes"`, `"no"`, `"case_by_case"`, `"unknown"`. Covers sponsorship for any jurisdiction (H-1B, Blue Card, Skilled Worker, etc.) — one field.

## Fields (time off / budget / perks)

- `annual_leave_days` — integer total days offered by the employer, or `null`. Capture the employer's figure; statutory minimums alone don't count unless the text specifies employer-granted extras.
- `annual_leave_unlimited` — `true` if "unlimited" (or equivalent); else `false` or `null`.
- `parental_leave_weeks` — only if the employer's contribution is stated. Statutory minimums don't count unless the text specifies the employer pays extra.
- `learning_budget_amount_year` — integer amount per year, or `null`. Use the currency already captured in `salary_currency` when ambiguous.
- `other_perks` — English-normalized tags for anything not captured above, e.g. `["commuter benefits", "mental health stipend", "gym membership", "pension contribution", "private healthcare"]`.

